President Muhammadu Buhari will on Friday, make a new year broadcast to the nation by 7:00 am. This was contained in a statement signed by Senior Special Assistant on Media and Publicity to President Buhari, Garba Shehu. He stated that television, radio, and other electronic media outlets are enjoined to join the network services of the Nigerian Television Authority (NTA) and Federal Radio Corporation of Nigeria (FRCN) respectively, for the broadcast.